The solitary sojourn upon an island is an extremely probable incident of Gildas’ lise; we see that he sighs for a retirement of this kind in the middle of his warfare. The Vita S. Cadoci, c. 29, also mentions this hermitage: ‘⁶ Cum beatus Gildas in insula Echni⁷' (c. 29); see also Vita ll, c. 9. The anchorite lise on the island mentioned in this passage may well have been a continuation of that which was begun on the island in the Eristol Channel. ln c. 28 it is called Horam, and by Breton writers is identified with the island llouat.
